<paragraph blockId="17.[136,1452,1336,1502]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
So far known from 
<collectingCountry box="[406,527,1441,1467]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[580,672,1441,1467]" name="Panama" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[682,849,1441,1467]" country="Panama" name="Bocas del Toro" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Bocas del Toro</collectingRegion>
(Reiner-Drehwald 2005). The specimen was included in a molecular phylogenetic analysis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Heinrichs, J. &amp; Dong, S. &amp; Schafer-Verwimp, A. &amp; Pocs, T. &amp; Feldberg, K. &amp; Czumaj, A. &amp; Schmidt, A. R. &amp; Reitner, J. &amp; Renner, M. A. M. &amp; Hentschel, J. &amp; Stech, M. &amp; Schneider, H." box="[582,838,1475,1502]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="82547" refId="ref23099" refString="Heinrichs, J., Dong, S., Schafer-Verwimp, A., Pocs, T., Feldberg, K., Czumaj, A., Schmidt, A. R., Reitner, J., Renner, M. A. M., Hentschel, J., Stech, M. &amp; Schneider, H. (2013) Molecular phylogeny of the leafy liverwort Lejeunea (Porellales): Evidence for a Neotropical origin, uneven distribution of sexual systems and insufficient taxonomy. PloS ONE 8 (12): e 82547. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0082547" type="journal article" year="2013">Heinrichs et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
